Mahmud Ghaznavi wasn’t a Pashtun or Afghan, his father Sebuktigin was a Turkic Mameluke from Kyrgyzstan and his mother is said to have been of Persian origin. Therefore by lineage he would also be considered Turkic. Sultan Mahmud Ghaznavi and the Ghaznavids were Persianised as well so they didn’t have Pashtun culture. Therefore to claim Sultan Mahmud Ghaznavi as an Afghan Pashtun is a lie.
